race.description: Carly Mae Pye Memorial Mdn Hcp
race.comment: Lots of these close to getting off the mark. EAST WEST MISS (10) is a former Victorian yet to hit the frame from six starts but does have figures good enough for this. Fitter for a trial and drawn to sit back and charge late fresh. Watch the market closely. RUN FREDA RUN (9) returned from a long break with a narrow miss over 1000m and strips fitter. Extra trip a plus and did run very well when last second-up in a similar race to this. DALT JAZ (5) has placed all four this time in and is long overdue. Drawn to feature again. THREE TEES (4) was solid fresh then improved to be beaten a whisker last time. Ready now and gets chance. THE BOSS MAN (1) is another former Victorian having first try for new yard. Has shown promise in just four starts and will take catching.
